Package com.avaya.cmapi

Contains ServiceProvider class which is the starting point to obtain access to any of the services provided in this API.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ServiceProviderListener
    Initiates an event listening for ServiceProvider These ServiceProvider events include: ServerConnectionDownEvent ServerSessionNotActiveEvent ServerSessionTerminatedEvent See Using Listeners in the Device, Media & Call Control (DMCC) API to learn more about how to use listeners.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApiPackageInfo
    Retrieves package information
    APIProtocolVersion  
    ServiceProvider
    The starting point to get access to CSTA services and the Avaya extensions to CSTA services.
    ServiceProviderAdapter
    Implements a "do nothing" callback method for each service provider event type.

Package com.avaya.cmapi Description

Contains ServiceProvider class which is the starting point to obtain access to any of the services provided in this API. All applications must start by using this package.
